  "texts": [
    "A subcanonical p-site a is such that κ 0a = F if and only if a = c F (I, A) for some A, A ⊃ F. Corollary 1.5.3 Let K ∈ P 2 (I).",
    "What are the subcanonical p-sites a ≡ c F (I, A) such that κ a = K?",
    "-If ∅ ∈ K,the solution is any one of the p-sites where F = K 0 and A ∈ P 2 (I), A ⊃ K 0, A ≠ K 0, in particular the solution F = K 0, A = K.-If ∅ ∉ K, the unique solution is the subcanonical p-site where F = A = K. Definition 1.5.4 The canonical p-site associated to the p-formation (I, A) is the p-site with foundational pair (I, A) and profile A i = {s ∈ A| i ∈ s}.",
    "It is denoted ca(I, A).",
    "A p-site a with base I is said to be canonical on I, if a = ca(I, A) for some I-complex A."
